{{Expand Romanian|Dacia (revistă de arheologie)|date=January 2011}} {{Infobox journal | title = Dacia | cover = | editor = | discipline = [[Archaeology|Archeology]] | language = French, English, German, Russian | abbreviation =Dacia | formernames = Dacia - Recherches et découvertes archéologiques en Roumanie | publisher = [[Vasile Pârvan Institute of Archaeology]] | country = [[Romania]] | frequency = | history = 1924-present | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://www.cimec.ro/arheologie/dacia_eng.htm | link1 = http://www.cimec.ro/scripts/dacia/selarticole.asp?Lang=EN | link1-name = online access | link2 = | link2-name = | JSTOR = | OCLC = | LCCN = | CODEN = | ISSN = 0070-251X | eISSN = }} '''''Dacia: Revistă arheologică și de istorie veche''''' is a [[Romania]]n [[academic journal]] of [[archeology]] published by the [[Vasile Pârvan Institute of Archaeology]], [[Bucharest]]. It was established in 1924 by the Romanian [[historian]] and archaeologist [[Vasile Pârvan]], in whose honor the institute was named. The original title of the journal was {{lang|fr|Dacia: Recherches et découvertes archéologiques en Roumanie}}. It has identical subsections in four languages: [[French language|French]], [[English language|English]], [[German language|German]] and [[Russian language|Russian]].
