'''Mousteroid''' was a culture occurring during the period 80,000 - 50,000 B.P. of Central,South and East Africa. Examples of this culture are the tool-industry of the [[Middle Paleolithic]] in [[West Africa]],<ref>O.Davies 1964</ref> <ref>J.D.Clark 1967)</ref> known from sites at Zenebi, [[Nigeria]] <ref>G.W.Barendson et al 1965</ref> and Tiemassas in [[Senegal]].<ref>(R.Guillot and C.Descamps 1969)</ref> <ref>C.T.SHAW THE PRE-HISTORY OF WEST AFRICA in Unesco International Scientific Committee for the Drafting of a General History of Africa ''General History of Africa: Methodology and African prehistory'' 819 pages [https://books.google.com/books?id=adjqADObNvMC&pg=PA621&lpg=PA621&dq=Mousteroid&source=bl&ots=MmI7-vVEa6&sig=THF5S9vbzQFTPvI-MpNQZD9URQA&hl=en&sa=X&ei=3lMLT6jwB4yHhQf0qKiVBA&sqi=2&ved=0CEQQ6AEwBQ#v=onepage&q=Mousteroid&f=false University of California Press, 1981 ] {{ISBN|0-435-94808-3}} [Retrieved 2012-01-09]</ref>
==Dakar and Rufisque== The most important of the Western Senegal sites is Pte. de Fann in [[Dakar]].<ref>Corbeil 1943</ref> Classified Mousteroid, indicating similarities to industry [[Mousterian]] in form but neither akin to, nor at a temporal parallel. Other sites about Dakar and [[Rufisque]], were part of a culture that had not occurred for sufficient duration for tools to be found at differing depths in the ground (''without [[Stratification (archeology)|stratification]]'')<ref>Oliver Davies ''West Africa before the Europeans: archaeology & prehistory'' - 364 pages ''Methuen's handbooks of archaeology'' references (Corbeil ''NA'' 17 (1943) [https://books.google.com/books?id=9TmlQLbpy9cC&pg=PA36&lpg=PA36&dq=Corbeil+R+western+senegal&source=bl&ots=JxWSEYIv8n&sig=KPLqguF_QmDlnXhbITk25ptPLQ8&hl=en&sa=X&ei=2VsLT_nzG9GD-wbKo83aDA&sqi=2&ved=0CB0Q6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=Corbeil%20R%20western%20senegal&f=false Corbeil R. , Mauny R. , Charbonnier J. , 1948 ], Richard 1955)[https://books.google.com/books?id=4aQOAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA141&lpg=PA141&dq=Mousteroid+of+Africa&source=bl&ots=t5w1xavaSe&sig=5Z9mUZrZ5GkgyOfLcmDOEzzSywk&hl=en&sa=X&ei=J1gLT4X7MoO6hAfNy5zIBA&sqi=2&ved=0CCYQ6AEwAg#v=onepage&q&f=false Taylor & Francis, 1967 ] [Retrieved 2012-01-09]</ref>
